        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 25 at 6:47PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 647 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northwest of Homer, or near Alto, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Airy, Alto, Raoul, Baldwin, and Cornelia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
